.TH LE-VIBE-SETUP-CLINE 1 "2026" "Linux" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
le-vibe-setup-cline \- install pinned Cline + YAML extensions for Lé Vibe
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B le-vibe-setup-cline
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs
.BR install\-cline\-extension.sh
(which installs pinned
.B saoudrizwan.claude-dev
and
.B redhat.vscode\-yaml
from Open VSX per
.BR docs/continue\-extension\-pin.md )
with clear exit codes (see below). Run as the desktop user after
.B lvibe
has completed first\-run
(same launcher as
.BR le\-vibe (1)).

\fBlvibe\fR invokes this command automatically only when \fBLE_VIBE_AUTO_CLINE_SETUP=1\fR (default off). See \fBlvibe\fR(1) / \fBle\-vibe\fR(1) DESCRIPTION.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 3
Extension install failed (Cline or YAML; network or marketplace).
.TP
.B 4
No editor binary (install VSCodium or set
.BR LE_VIBE_EDITOR ).
.TP
.B 127
Helper scripts not found.
.TP
.B 125
Unknown CLI option (see
.BR \-\-help ).
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lvibe (1),
.BR le\-vibe (1),
.BR codium (1).
.PP
Full post\-install steps and policy summary: \fI/usr/share/doc/le\-vibe/README.Debian\fR.
